card-date\" datetime=\"2025-03-25\">25 Mar 2025</time>\n                <!--\n         --></footer>\n        </div>\n    </a>","link":"https://www.devas.life/how-i-implemented-totp-based-2fa-for-my-markdown-note-app/","retrieved":1742860800000},{"title":"Answering dev questions based on my tech notes using MCP + Claude","contents":"<a class=\"gh-card-link\" href=\"/answering-dev-questions-based-on-my-tech-notes-using-mcp-claude/\">\n            <figure class=\"gh-card-image\">\n                <img srcset=\"/content/images/size/w160/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-18-Answering-questions-using-MCP_kanji.png 160w,\n                            /content/images/size/w320/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-18-Answering-questions-using-MCP_kanji.png 320w,\n                            /content/images/size/w600/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-18-Answering-questions-using-MCP_kanji.png 600w,\n                            /content/images/size/w960/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-18-Answering-questions-using-MCP_kanji.png 960w,\n                            /content/images/size/w1200/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-18-Answering-questions-using-MCP_kanji.png 1200w,\n                            /content/images/size/w2000/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-18-Answering-questions-using-MCP_kanji.png 2000w\" sizes=\"320px\" src=\"/content/images/size/w600/2025/03/25-03-18-Answering-questions-using-MCP_kanji.png\" alt=\"Answering dev questions based on my tech notes using MCP + Claude\" loading=\"lazy\">\n            </figure>\n        <div class=\"gh-card-wrapper\">\n            <h3 class=\"gh-card-title is-title\">Answering dev questions based on my tech notes using MCP + Claude</h3>\n                    <p class=\"gh-card-excerpt is-body\">In the previous post, I integrated my note-taking app Inkdrop with Claude's MCP:\n\nIntegrating my note app with Claude‚Äôs MCPHi, it‚Äôs Takuya here. I‚Äôve been fiddling with Claude, which provides an interesting protocol for third-party AI integrations called MCP (Model Context Protocol). Some of my</p>\n            <footer class=\"gh-card-meta\">\n<!--\n             -->\n                    <span class=\"gh-card-author\">By Takuya Matsuyama</span>\n                    <time class=\"gh-card-date\" datetime=\"2025-03-18\">18 Mar 2025</time>\n                <!--\n         --></footer>\n        </div>\n    </a>","link":"https://www.devas.life/answering-dev-questions-based-on-my-tech-notes-using-mcp-claude/","retrieved":1742256000000},{"title":"Integrating my note app with Claude's MCP","contents":"<a class=\"gh-card-link\" href=\"/integrating-my-note-app-with-claudes-mcp/\">\n            <figure class=\"gh-card-image\">\n                <img srcset=\"/content/images/size/w160/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-07-MCP-Integration_thumb.jpg 160w,\n                            /content/images/size/w320/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-07-MCP-Integration_thumb.jpg 320w,\n                            /content/images/size/w600/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-07-MCP-Integration_thumb.jpg 600w,\n                            /content/images/size/w960/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-07-MCP-Integration_thumb.jpg 960w,\n                            /content/images/size/w1200/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-07-MCP-Integration_thumb.jpg 1200w,\n                            /content/images/size/w2000/format/webp/2025/03/25-03-07-MCP-Integration_thumb.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"320px\" src=\"/content/images/size/w600/2025/03/25-03-07-MCP-Integration_thumb.jpg\" alt=\"Integrating my note app with Claude's MCP\" loading=\"lazy\">\n            </figure>\n        <div class=\"gh-card-wrapper\">\n            <h3 class=\"gh-card-title is-title\">Integrating my note app with Claude's MCP</h3>\n                    <p class=\"gh-card-excerpt is-body\">Hi, it's Takuya here. I've been fiddling with Claude, which provides an interesting protocol for third-party AI integrations called MCP (Model Context Protocol). Some of my note app (called Inkdrop) users requested that they want to let Claude use their tech notes as knowledge via MCP.</p>\n            <footer class=\"gh-card-meta\">\n<!--\n             -->\n                    <span class=\"gh-card-author\">By Takuya Matsuyama</span>\n                    <time class=\"gh-card-date\" datetime=\"2025-03-07\">07 Mar 2025</time>\n                <!--\n         --></footer>\n        </div>\n    </a>","link":"https://www.devas.life/integrating-my-note-app-with-claudes-mcp/","retrieved":1741305600000},{"title":"How to animate a TanStack Virtual list with Motion","contents":"<a class=\"gh-card-link\" href=\"/how-to-animate-a-tanstack-virtual-list-with-motion/\">\n            <figure class=\"gh-card-image\">\n                <img srcset=\"/content/images/size/w160/format/webp/2025/02/25-02-27_note-list-animations_thumb2.jpg 160w,\n                            /content/images/size/w320/format/webp/2025/02/25-02-27_note-list-animations_thumb2.jpg 320w,\n                            /content/images/size/w600/format/webp/2025/02/25-02-27_note-list-animations_thumb2.jpg 600w,\n                            /content/images/size/w960/format/webp/2025/02/25-02-27_note-list-animations_thumb2.jpg 960w,\n                            /content/images/size/w1200/format/webp/2025/02/25-02-27_note-list-animations_thumb2.jpg 1200w,\n                            /content/images/size/w2000/format/webp/2025/02/25-02-27_note-list-animations_thumb2.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"320px\" src=\"/content/images/size/w600/2025/02/25-02-27_note-list-animations_thumb2.jpg\" alt=\"How to animate a TanStack Virtual list with Motion\" loading=\"lazy\">\n            </figure>\n        <div class=\"gh-card-wrapper\">\n            <h3 class=\"gh-card-title is-title\">How to animate a TanStack Virtual list with Motion</h3>\n                    <p class=\"gh-card-excerpt is-body\">I love Motion. It makes animating UIs in web apps incredibly easy. I've been using it in my app to animate components like the tags input bar, the notebook list, dialogs, and more.\n\nOne of the components I wanted